Select desired FSS interface

This enumerator defines the valid interface selections for the FSS. Note that for fss_ul, only CSL_FSS_INTERFACE_SELECT_FSAS is valid.

typedef uint32_t CSL_FssInterfaceSelect
 
#define CSL_FSS_INTERFACE_SELECT_FSAS   ((uint32_t) 0U)
 
#define CSL_FSS_INTERFACE_SELECT_FSS   ((uint32_t) 1U)
 

Select desired path for the FSAS interface

This enumerator selects the desired path (OSPI0 or HYPERBUS) for the FSAS interface. Note that for fss_ul, only CSL_FSS_FSAS_INTERFACE_PATH_SELECT_OSPI0 is valid.

typedef uint32_t CSL_FssFsasInterfacePathSelect
 
#define CSL_FSS_FSAS_INTERFACE_PATH_SELECT_OSPI0   ((uint32_t) 0U)
 
#define CSL_FSS_FSAS_INTERFACE_PATH_SELECT_HYPERBUS   ((uint32_t) 1U)

Macro Definition Documentation

#define CSL_FSS_FSAS_INTERFACE_PATH_SELECT_OSPI0   ((uint32_t) 0U)

Select path to HyperBus

#define CSL_FSS_INTERFACE_SELECT_FSAS   ((uint32_t) 0U)

Select FSS interface (to OSPI1)

#define CSL_FSS_INTERRUPT_SOURCE_SELECT_ECC_ERROR_1BIT   ((uint32_t) 0U)

ECC error on 2 bits, not correctable

#define CSL_FSS_INTERRUPT_SOURCE_SELECT_ECC_ERROR_2BIT   ((uint32_t) 1U)

Write is not aligned to 32B boundary or not a multiple of 32B

#define CSL_FSS_OTFA_CRYPTO_CORE_ALLOCATION_BALANCED   ((uint32_t) 0U)

Read optimized: 75% of the cypto cores alocated to the Read Pipe, 25% of the Cypto cores on the Write Pipe

#define CSL_FSS_OTFA_CRYPTO_CORE_ALLOCATION_RD_OPTIMIZED   ((uint32_t) 1U)

Write optimized: 25% of the cypto cores alocated to the Read Pipe, 75% of the Cypto cores on the Write Pipe

#define CSL_FSS_OTFA_ENC_MODE_AES_CTR   ((uint32_t) 1U)

ECB+ mode

#define CSL_FSS_OTFA_ENC_MODE_DISABLED   ((uint32_t) 0U)

AES CTR mode

#define CSL_FSS_OTFA_INTERRUPT_SOURCE_SELECT_CTR_WKV   ((uint32_t) 0U)

Region overflow boundary event caused by a burst transaction crossing a start or end of a region

#define CSL_FSS_OTFA_INTERRUPT_SOURCE_SELECT_REGION_BV   ((uint32_t) 1U)

Region write error event, write cmd issues when write is disabled

#define CSL_FSS_OTFA_INTERRUPT_SOURCE_SELECT_WRITE_ERR   ((uint32_t) 2U)

Region MAC compare error event, read MAC did not match the write MAC

#define CSL_FSS_OTFA_KEY_SIZE_128_BITS   ((uint32_t) 0U)

256-bit key size

#define CSL_FSS_OTFA_MAC_MODE_DISABLED   ((uint32_t) 0U)

GMAC mode, max burst size of 128 Bytes

#define CSL_FSS_OTFA_MAC_MODE_GMAC   ((uint32_t) 1U)

CBC-MAC mode, max burst size of 128 Bytes

32 byte aligned block address

uint32_t CSL_FssWrErrorInfo::addr

Crypto core allocation. See CSL_FssOtfaCrypoCoreAlloc

Indicates the Route ID for the Master that caused the write error

Master seq which caused the event. Not avalible for MAC error events.

Key size. See CSL_FssOtfaKeySize

uint32_t CSL_FssEccBlockErrorInfo::da0

When set indicates that there was a single error detected within the High Data word

uint32_t CSL_FssEccBlockErrorInfo::da1

When set indicates that there was a single error detected within the MAC field

uint32_t CSL_FssEccBlockErrorInfo::ded

When set indicates that there was a single error detected within the Low Data word

uint32_t CSL_FssOtfaCryptoRegionCfg::encKey[8]

Defines the Encryption Prime key (decryption key) when ECB+ mode is enabled. Used only during read operations. SW must generate the encPrimeKey based on encKey.

uint32_t CSL_FssOtfaCryptoRegionCfg::encMode

Defines the base address of the MAC signatures. Must be 4KB aligned.

uint32_t CSL_FssOtfaCryptoRegionCfg::encPrimeKey[8]

Defines the Authentication key for GMAC modes. For CBC-MAC modes, this key is only used for write operations.

uint32_t CSL_FssOtfaIrqInfo::id

Master cmd which caused the event

uint32_t CSL_FssOtfaIrqInfo::length

Master address which caused the event

uint32_t CSL_FssEccBlockErrorInfo::mac

When set indicates that there was a single error detected within the address field

uint32_t CSL_FssOtfaCryptoRegionCfg::macKey[4]

Defines the CBC-MAC Prime key (decryption key) when CBC-MAC mode is enabled. Used only during read operations. SW must generate the macPrimeKey based on macKey.

uint32_t CSL_FssOtfaCryptoRegionCfg::macMode

Defines the Encryption mode. See CSL_FssOtfaEncMode

uint32_t CSL_FssOtfaCryptoRegionCfg::macPrimeKey[4]

Defines the Initialization Vector used for Encryption/Authentication

uint32_t CSL_FssOtfaCryptoRegionCfg::macSignaturesBaseAddr

Defines the start of the crypto memory region. Must be 4KB aligned.

uint32_t CSL_FssCfg::otfaKeySizeWords

Pointer to the OTFA configuration register region

CSL_fss_fsas_genregsRegs* CSL_FssCfg::pFsasRegs

Pointer to the FSS configuration register region

CSL_fss_fsas_otfa_regsRegs* CSL_FssCfg::pOtfaRegs

Pointer to the FSAS configuration register region

uint32_t CSL_FssOtfaCryptoRegionCfg::regionAddrStart

Defines the size of the crypto memory region. Must be a multiple of 4KB.

uint32_t CSL_FssOtfaCryptoRegionCfg::regionSizeBytes

Defines the Encryption key for AES-CTR modes. For AES ECB+ modes, this key is only used for write operations.

uint32_t CSL_FssOtfaStats::rmEventCnt

Number of cache miss events

uint32_t CSL_FssOtfaStats::rmwEventCnt

Number of RM events

uint32_t CSL_FssEccBlockErrorInfo::sec

When set indicates that there was a double error detected for the block

uint32_t CSL_FssOtfaIrqInfo::seq

Master burst length which caused the event

uint32_t CSL_FssOtfaCryptoRegionCfg::writeProtect

< Write protection mode: 0=disabled, otherwise enabled. When enabled, all write cmds will get forwarded with their byte enables nullified. Also a WRITE_ERR event will get set for that region which had the violation. Defines the Authentication mode. See CSL_FssOtfaMacMode
